==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stour
<hw>Stour</hw> <pr>(stour <it>or</it> st⟦oomac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OF. <ets>estour</ets>, <ets>estor</ets>, tumult, combat, of
Teutonic origin. See <er>Storm</er>.]</ety> <def>A battle or tumult;
encounter; combat; disturbance; passion.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<au>Fairfax.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧That woeful <xex>stowre</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She that helmed was in starke <qex>stours</qex> [fierce
conflicts].</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stour</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stour
<hw>Stour</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Stoor</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Tall; strong; stern.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
